extracted info: {'explanation': "The bug occurs in DataSet.update method where chunked dask DataArray gets evaluated eagerly and loses its chunked structure. Additionally, there's an issue with Dataset constructor where creating a Dataset with DataArray and dimension names causes computation of the dask array, converting it from dask.array.core.Array to numpy.ndarray.", 'identifiers': ['DataSet', 'update', 'Dataset', 'DataArray'], 'code snippet': 'foo = xr.DataArray(np.random.randn(3, 3), dims=("x", "y")).chunk()  # foo is chunked
ds = xr.Dataset({"foo": foo, "bar": ("x", [1, 2, 3])})  # foo is still chunked here
ds  # you can verify that foo is chunked
update_dict = {"foo": (("x", "y"), ds.foo[1:, :]), "bar": ("x", ds.bar[1:])}
ds.update(update_dict)
ds  # now foo is no longer chunked'}

